# Splunk REST tokens — local development template.
#
# 1. Copy this file to `secrets.env` (which IS gitignored).
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with bearer tokens minted in your
#    own Splunk instance(s) under Settings → Tokens. Tokens grant API
#    access; treat them like passwords. Never commit `secrets.env`.
# 3. Source the file before running tooling that talks to Splunk:
#       set -a && source secrets.env && set +a
#
# Naming convention: SPLUNK_<HOST_NICKNAME>_TOKEN. Add as many as you
# need; tooling reads them by environment variable name.
#
# These environment variables are consumed by:
# - scripts/run_uc_tests.py        — UC SPL execution against a Splunk
#                                    instance (read-only search jobs).
# - scripts/audit_splunk_cloud_compat.py — REST API metadata audit.
# - mcp/src/splunk_uc_mcp/        — optional Splunk REST integration in
#                                    the MCP server (currently disabled
#                                    by default; the catalogue is
#                                    served from local JSON).

# Example: search head named "rev" at 192.0.2.45 (illustrative)
SPLUNK_REST_TOKEN=replace-with-your-search-head-bearer-token

# Example: indexer named "mink" at 192.0.2.158 (illustrative)
SPLUNK_MINK_TOKEN=replace-with-your-indexer-bearer-token
